The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 02 March is 40,313 (4,666 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 25 February, there were 623 new confirmed cases (72.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 18 February, there were 764 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 18% (141 fewer cases).
